answer.body:
IPOS would like to encourage the complainant to seek amicable settlements before making a complaint to IPOS so as to save time and avoid unnecessary legal costs. The complainant has various options to resolve the case: 

(i) The Association of Singapore Patent Agents ("ASPA"), if the complainant?s patent agent is a member of ASPA; 

(ii) The patent agent's firm's complaint procedure, if available; 

(iii) The Law Society of Singapore, if the complainant?s patent agent is a Singapore lawyer; or 

(iv) The Singapore Mediation Centre. Mediation is a voluntary process in which a third party (called the mediator) facilitates negotiations between the disputing parties with a view to resolving their differences privately and amicably.
